        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I ran into this testing my code using both Zend_Uri_Http and Zend_Http_Client. Since the client mutates the argument, setting the port to a default port (See ZF-11162), it was hard for me to assert equality between expected URI's and actual URI's in my unit test.\r\n\r\nImho, it would be nicer if Zend_Uri_Http ignores the port number in the constructed string URL if it is the default for the current scheme. See the provided patch and unit test.\r\n\r\nMaybe there should be an option 'ignoreDefaultPorts' or an argument for the getUri() method, I'm not sure."
        },
